column5: It's Cicada time. One of many types in North America.  http://www.ctvnews.ca/sci-tech/17-year-cicada-hatch-to-bring-billions-of-bugs-to-u-s-east-coast-1.1238606
Yup, been reading about that!!  Looking forward to their beautiful song !!
Same here there is gonna be millions of them !!! I seen a segment on the discovery channel about it !!! Going to be a lot of noise for sure .....lookin forward to it
Gonna be a brown trout bonanza when those buggers start to emerge
They get to 'do it' once every 17 years. Slightly less than some married guys!
Yes, makes you think....All the wonderful sounds of nature are animals and bugs trying desperately to get fed or laid...
